<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-839-704  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 839 704.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Data Communications  Sept 1990 v19 n11 p58(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Host, switches announce engagement, plan nuptials.andO;(host-to-switch-interfaces)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Jander, Mary.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Host and switch manufacturers are presenting a new group ofapplication program interfaces (APIs) that are linking centraloffice switches or PBXs (Private Branch Exchange) with hostcomputers.andP;  A standards movement is being formed that may in thefuture permit one application, using many types of telephoneswitches, to run on a range of host platforms.andP;  These types ofAPIs would allow customers to retain their present equipment.andP;  AT1S1 sub-committee of the American National Standards Institute(ANSI) is attempting to define a set of specifications calledSwitch-to-Computer API (SCAI).andP;  This would provide a common groundfor any host to effectively communicate with any switch.andP;  ATandamp;T'sAdjunct/Switch Application Interface (ASAI) is a set ofspecifications created by ATandamp;T incorporating standard signalingprotocols and conventions to name elements remotely accessed byinterface software.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     Digital communicationsTelecommunication Switching SystemsApplications Programming InterfaceStandardization.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Major host-to-switch interfaces. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>